Many people in the Hamilton community were almost offended by this piece of sculpture, and yet it makes its point enormously eloquently.  
I should say that Hamilton is an industrial town. 
It has two major steel corporations and a number of heavy industries. 
I hate to say it, but industrial accidents are not an infrequent occurrence. 
Fortunately they are much rarer than they used to be 20, 30 or 40 years ago, but they still occur.  
